doc.after: The Commonwealth Secretariat established in 1965 is the main intergovernmental agency of the Commonwealth facilitating consultation and co operation among member governments and countries It is responsible to member governments collectively The Commonwealth of Nations is represented in the United Nations General Assembly by the secretariat as an observer The secretariat organises Commonwealth summits meetings of ministers consultative meetings and technical discussions it assists policy development and provides policy advice and facilitates multilateral communication among the member governments It also provides technical assistance to help governments in the social and economic development of their countries and in support of the Commonwealth s fundamental political values
